5 9. "Unmanned aerial vehicle" means any aerial vehicle that is operated without the
6 possibility of direct human intervention within or on the aerial vehicle. The term does
7 not include satellites.
8 5.10. "Unmanned aerial vehicle system" means an unmanned aerial vehicle and associated
9 elements, including communication links and the components that control the
10 unmanned aerial vehicle, which are required for the pilot in command to operate safely
11 and efficiently in state airspace.
12 SECTION 2. AMENDMENT. Section 29-29.4-02 of the North Dakota Century Code is
13 amended and reenacted as follows:
14 29-29.4-02. Limitations on use of unmanned aerial vehicle systemsystems and
15 robots.
16 1. Information obtained from an unmanned aerial vehicle or robot is not admissible in a
17 prosecution or proceeding within the state unless the information was obtained:
18 a. Pursuant to the authority of a search warrant; or
19 b. In accordance with exceptions to the warrant requirement.
20 2. Information obtained from the operation of an unmanned aerial vehicle or robot may
21 not be used in an affidavit of probable cause in an effort to obtain a search warrant,
22 unless the information was obtained under the circumstances described in subdivision
23 a or b of subsection 1 or was obtained through the monitoring of public lands or
24 international borders.
25 SECTION 3. AMENDMENT. Section 29-29.4-03 of the North Dakota Century Code is
26 amended and reenacted as follows:
27 29-29.4-03. Warrant requirements.
28 A warrant for the use of an unmanned aerial vehicle or robot for the purpose of surveillance
29 must satisfy the requirements of the Constitution of North Dakota. In addition, the warrant must
30 contain a data collection statement that includes:
