12 SECTION 5. AMENDMENT. Section 29-29.4-05 of the North Dakota Century Code is
13 amended and reenacted as follows:
14 29-29.4-05. Prohibited use - Exceptions.
15 1. A law enforcement agency may not authorize the use of, including granting a permit to
16 use, an unmanned aerial vehicle armed with any lethal weapons.
17 2. This chapter prohibits any use of an unmanned aerial vehicle or robot for:
18 a. Domestic use in private surveillance. A law enforcement agency may not
19 authorize the use of, including granting a permit to use, an unmanned aerial
20 vehicle or robot to permit any private person to conduct surveillance on any other
21 private person without the express, informed consent of that other person or the
22 owner of any real property on which that other private person is present.
23 b. Surveillance of the lawful exercise of constitutional rights, unless the surveillance
24 is otherwise allowed under this chapter.
25 3. A law enforcement agency may not authorize the use of a robot to deploy a lethal
26 weapon, unless the weapon is controlled remotely, cannot be activated autonomously,
27 and is used to:
28 a. Neutralize an inanimate object at risk of exploding or causing an immediate
29 threat to public safety or property; or
