1 b. Prevent an imminent and substantial risk of serious bodily injury or death to a law
2 enforcement officer or another individual, in a circumstance where the use of
3 lethal force by an officer would be legally justified.
4 4. A law enforcement agency may not authorize the use of an unmanned aerial vehicle or
5 robot to deploy a less than lethal weapon, unless the weapon is controlled remotely
6 and cannot be activated autonomously.
7 5. A law enforcement agency, before authorizing any use of force, shall adopt a policy on
8 the use of force by an unmanned aerial vehicle or robot, which includes the individuals
9 with authority to authorize the use of force by an unmanned aerial vehicle or robot.
10 SECTION 6. AMENDMENT. Section 29-29.4-06 of the North Dakota Century Code is
11 amended and reenacted as follows:
12 29-29.4-06. Documentation of unmanned aerial vehicle or robot use.
13 1. The person authorized to conduct the surveillance under this chapter shall document
14 all use of an unmanned aerial vehicle or robot for surveillance. The person shall
15 document all surveillance flights as to duration, flight path, and mission objectives.
16 2. The flight information must be verified as accurate and complete by the supervising
17 person authorized by a court to conduct the surveillance.
18 3. The flight information required under this section must be retained for five years.
19 4. Any imaging or any other forms of data lawfully obtained under this chapter which are
20 not accompanied by a reasonable and articulable suspicion that the images or data
21 contain evidence of a crime, or are relevant to an ongoing investigation or trial, may
22 not be retained for more than ninety days.
23 5. Except for the operational capabilities of the unmanned aerial vehicle system or robot
24 and other operational information strictly related to the technical conduct and physical
25 security of the surveillance operation, a person accused of a crime that includes
26 evidence gathered through the use of an unmanned aerial vehicle system or robot
27 surveillance may obtain all information relating to the person acquired in the course of
28 the surveillance through subpoena and discovery proceedings available in criminal
29 proceedings.
30 6. A law enforcement agency deploying a robot armed with a lethal weapon shall
31 document the requirements provided in section 29 - 29.4 - 05 .
